HEADWORD: Flitting
<hw>Flit"ting</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A flying
with lightness and celerity; a fluttering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A removal from one habitation to another.</def>
<mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A neighbor had lent his cart for the <qex>flitting</qex>, and it
was now standing loaded at the door, ready to move away.</q>
<rj><qau>Jeffrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

